1 on 25 january 2007, i ordered that the defendant company be wound up and that the provisional liquidator of that company, mr barry hamilton, be appointed as liquidator.
i made the orders that mr hamilton sought, and indicated that i would provide reasons for making both the winding up orders and the orders sought by mr hamilton at a later date.
following his appointment as liquidator, in his capacity as liquidator and on behalf of the defendant company in liquidation, mr hamilton sought orders relating to some funds allegedly paid by the defendant to a third company, casino busters international.